-- Aqua America’s Texas Unit Plans $17.1 Million in Water Upgrades
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-07-03T16:20:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-03/aqua-america-s-texas-unit-plans-17-1-million-in-water-upgrades.html
Aqua America Inc. (WTR) ’s Texas unit is
planning $17.1 million in water and sewer infrastructure
improvements this year, more than two-thirds of the upgrades
designated for its southern operating divisions, it said today.  Aqua Texas Inc. provides water and wastewater services to
about 177,000 residents across the state, the company said in a
statement. Aqua America is the second-largest publicly traded
water utility in the U.S. after American Water Works Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
